.TH "mem_cgroup_update_lru_size" 9 "mem_cgroup_update_lru_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mem_cgroup_update_lru_size \- account for adding or removing an lru page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mem_cgroup_update_lru_size
.BI "(struct lruvec *lruvec "  ","
.BI "enum lru_list lru "  ","
.BI "int zid "  ","
.BI "int nr_pages "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lruvec" 12
mem_cgroup per zone lru vector
.IP "lru" 12
index of lru list the page is sitting on
.IP "zid" 12
zone id of the accounted pages
.IP "nr_pages" 12
positive when adding or negative when removing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must be called under lru_lock, just before a page is added
to or just after a page is removed from an lru list (that ordering being
so as to allow it to check that lru_size 0 is consistent with list_empty).
